Sweet 16 Browning made in Belguim stamped on the barrel.  FN on buttstock.  This is by far the smoothest shooting shotgun I've ever owned.  Retired it to the safe about 20 years ago.  It was in my grandpa's gun safe for about 30 years.  Gold trigger, sweet sixteen receiver, in almost Mint condition!  The wood is absolutely stunning with a honey golden brown color/sheen to it.  It's a collectible and always will be.  Original plug is included.  Ribbed barrel, gold trigger and front sight, Auto-5 action that's as smooth as butter.Made around 1964, and was a special order since it's a round knob.  No cracks on the forend visible to the naked eye anyway.  I don't have a loop but this Sweet 16 is literally near mint and has never been refinished or restained.  The blueing is 99% perfect!  It's all original and I'm told by gunners all the time that it's the nicest/cleanest Sweet 16 they've ever seen.  Then people beg me not to sell it.  However, I really need it to go to a new home and be loved by another.
